# Writer Copy Is Immutable on Blog Publish

When a user provides blog draft copy and asks to publish it, treat the supplied body text as immutable.

## Non-negotiable

- Do not rewrite, summarize, condense, reorder, or "optimize" article body copy.
- Do not change headings, numbers, named businesses, quotes, or punctuation in the body.
- Keep paragraph order and section structure exactly as supplied.

## Allowed edits (technical publishing only)

- Frontmatter-equivalent metadata (`postsMeta.ts`): slug, title, description, dates, keywords, author slug.
- Registry wiring: `postLoaders.ts`, `postFaqs.ts`, share image mapping, related metadata files.
- SEO/AEO technical implementation: schema wiring, canonical/meta generation via existing system, sitemap/llms artifacts from build.
- Build/prerender/release-gate fixes that do not alter supplied body text.

## If a change seems required

- If a technical constraint appears to require touching body copy, stop and ask the user before changing any copy.
- Prefer implementation workarounds that preserve the exact source text.
